I would recommend you get vaccinated.  It is highly likely that if either your brother or mother catch it that you will as well and if you are unvaccinated it is much more likely that your symptoms will be severe and require hospitalization.  As they are both in public frequently and around unvaccinated folk it is also rather likely that they will come into contact and because they are vaccinated could easily pass it to you without showing symptoms.  

&#x200B;

Please get vaccinated.

Canadian healthcare sounds awesome.

&#x200B;

Sorry you're going through this... but I think you need to see a different rheumatologist. Also a physiotherapist. The best way to stabilize your joints is by strengthening muscles around them, not medications or surgery. Also might try wearing splints to stabilize those joints which can be splinted.
